Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_path_exceptions(25.10)                    report_path_exceptions(25.10)

Name
       report_path_exceptions - Generates a report about path exceptions spec-
       ified  using  the  set_false_path,  set_min_delay,  set_max_delay,  and
       set_multicycle_path commands

Syntax
        report_path_exceptions

       [-help]

       [-all]

       [-early | -late]

       [-ignored]

       [-view <view_name>]

       [{> | >>} <filename> | -tcl_list]

       Generates  a  report  about  path  exceptions   specified   using   the
       set_false_path,  set_min_delay,  set_max_delay, and set_multicycle_path
       commands.

       By default, the report_path_exceptions command only  reports  activated
       path  exceptions. To report only the path exceptions that have been ig-
       nored by timing analysis, specify the -ignored parameter.

       If more than one path exception is applied on a timing  path,  multiple
       path exceptions that match a given path are prioritized. The adjustment
       on the path honors the path exception with the highest priority.

       When  the  software is in multi-mode multi-corner timing analysis mode,
       the report generates path exception information for every active analy-
       sis view.

       The report_path_exceptions command output also includes 2 columns  that
       show  the  file name and line number. The report output shows the exact
       file name and line number of the applied/ignored constraints. The  com-
       pressed  constraints will be decompressed first and then shown as indi-
       vidual constraints as written in the SDC file.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out command usage.

       -all   Reports all the applied and ignored path exceptions.

       {> | >>} <filename>
              When specified with >, writes the report to the  specified  file
              name. If the file already exists, the software overwrites it.

              When  specified with >>, writes the report to the specified file
              name. If the file already exists, the software concatenates  the
              report to the end of the file.

              The  <filename> parameter must be the last argument in the list.
              The <filename> and -tcl_list parameters are mutually  exclusive;
              you cannot specify them together.

              Note: To write a compressed report, add the .gz extension to the
              file name.

              Default:  Report  is  displayed on standard output without being
              saved.

       -early | -late
              Generates the path exception report for either  early  paths  or
              late paths.

              Default: Generates a report based on the current timing analysis
              mode.

       -ignored
              Reports  only the path exceptions that have been ignored by tim-
              ing analysis. This parameter can  be  used  for  debugging  con-
              straints  that may be ineffective or incorrectly entered. A path
              exception may be ineffective if it is covered by, or  overridden
              by, another path exception. For example:

              set_false_path -to OUT

              set_multicycle_path -to OUT 2

              In  the  above scenario, the set_multicycle_path command will be
              ignored as false paths have higher priority over cycle  addition
              on the same timing paths.

       -tcl_list
              Produces the report in Tcl list format instead of a tabular for-
              mat. This is useful for integrating timing with custom Tcl func-
              tions, and also for customizing report generation.

              The  -tcl_list and <filename> parameters are mutually exclusive;
              you cannot specify them together.

       -view <view_name>
              Generates a path exception report  for  the  specified  analysis
              view only. You can specify this parameter only when the software
              is in multi-mode multi-corner timing analysis mode.

Examples
              * The  following  commands  shows that a false path has priority
                over cycle addition on the same path:

                set_false_path -from seg1/u3/CK -to seg1/u9/d

                set_multicycle_path -from seg1/u3/CK -to seg1/u9/D 2

                > report_path_exception -ignored

                ------------------------------------------------------

                From       To          Early           Late

                -----------------------------------------------------

                seg1/u3/CK  seg1/u9/D   false ignored   false ignored

                seg1/u3/CK  seg1/u9/D   -               add 1 ignored

                seg1/u3/CK  seg1/u9/D   add 0 ignored   -

                -----------------------------------------------------

                The following command shows how edges are handled:

                set_false_path -rise_from {IN1} -through {OUT1}

                set_false_path -rise_from {IN1 IN2} -fall_to {OUT1}

                set_false_path -rise_from {IN1}

                tempus> report_path_exceptions -ignored

                -------------------------------------------------------------

                From        Through    To      Early            Late

                -------------------------------------------------------------

                ^ IN1 IN2   -          v OUT1  false ignored   false ignored

                ^ IN1       OUT1       -       false ignored   false ignored

                -------------------------------------------------------------

                > report_path_exceptions -early

                ------------------------------------

                From       Through    To  Early

                ------------------------------------

                ^ IN1      -          -   false

                ------------------------------------

                tempus> report_path_exceptions -late

                ------------------------------------

                From   Through  To  Late

                ------------------------------

                ^ IN1  -       -    false

                ------------------------------

                When the software is in multi-mode multi-corner timing  analy-
                sis  mode,  the  software generates path exception information
                for every active analysis view:

                set_analysis_view -setup {setup1 setup2} -hold {hold1 hold2}

                > report_path_exceptions

                -----------------------------------------

                From              Early  Late     View

                                                  Name

                -----------------------------------------

                test_mode reset  false           setup2

                test_mode reset  false           setup1

                test_mode reset         false    hold1

                test_mode reset         false    hold2

                ----------------------------------------

                Specify the -view parameter to generate a report  only  for  a
                specific active analysis view:

                > report_path_exceptions -view setup1

                --------------------------------------------

                From       Early    Late     View

                                             Name

                --------------------------------------

                test_mode reset    false     setup1

                --------------------------------------

